<td valign=top bgcolor=#FFFFCC class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/umareerevivisco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maree Revivisco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#000000>(1/12/02 10:28:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=170.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Rez... or not to Rez...</span><hr size=1> If I am in the same zone as you and you drag me the body then I will res you...I also have my epic. <br>
<br>
Before I had my epic if I was grouped and someone asked me for a res I would *always* /g do you mind if I res this person? <br>
<br>
For those of you who have never played a cleric a res takes *ALOT* of mana to do...and then I personally feel obligated to heal this person to a decent amount of HPs, otherwise one lousy hit on them and I am doing another res. So just assuming that you dropped your body at a clerics feet you don't owe them anything...think again. <br>
<br>
Now that I do have my epic I do the drive by reses just like several of the other clerics have stated here...I will also zone for you *if* I am not busy. If you offer me money to do it I am much more inclined to do it. Once I have to 1) hunt down the body 2) zone to get to the body this negates the fact it is a manaless res  (although it still takes mana to heal you) <br>
<br>
I do not charge for reses if you offer me a donation then I will do it...if you /auc an insane amount of pp to go to some far off zone to res you and I am not busy heck ya I'll go. [bold]Clerics are poor, peridots are expensive[/bold]<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Mar<br>
